what is the default leader in neovim

Gemini said
In Neovim, the default leader key is actually the backslash key (\).

Most users find it a bit awkward to reach, which is why almost every Neovim configuration you’ll see on GitHub or Reddit immediately changes it to something more accessible.

How to check your current Leader
If you aren't sure if your config has already changed it, you can run this command inside Neovim:

Vim Script
:lua print(vim.g.mapleader or "default (\\)")
Why people change it
The backslash is tucked away near the Enter or Backspace key depending on your keyboard layout. Since the "Leader" key is meant to be the prefix for your most-used custom commands, you want it somewhere your fingers naturally rest.

The Popular Alternatives
The most common choice by far is the Spacebar. It’s the biggest key on your board, and your thumbs are usually just sitting there doing nothing in Normal mode.

To change it in your init.lua, add this at the very top of the file (before your plugins load):

Lua
-- Set space as the leader key
vim.g.mapleader = " "
vim.g.maplocalleader = " " -- Often used for buffer-specific mappings
Why "Space" is the GOAT (Greatest of All Time):
Ergonomics: No pinky-stretching required.

Visibility: In many status lines or command areas, a space is easy to "see" as a pending input.

Speed: It turns your keybindings into rhythmic sequences, like Space -> f -> f to find a file.

